================================================================================
SKITECH. INFRASTRUCTURE & BACKEND INFRASTRUCTURE
================================================================================

I. BACKEND STRUCTURE (PROPOSED EXPRESS/NODE.JS ARCHITECTURE)
------------------------------------------------------------

/backend
├── config/             # Database (Mongoose), Cloudinary, JWT config
├── middleware/         # Auth, Role validation, Error handler, Rate limiting
├── controllers/        # Logical handlers (authController, houseController, itemController, adminController)
├── models/             # Mongoose schemas (User, House, Item, Notification, Rating)
├── routes/             # API entry points (v1/auth, v1/houses, v1/items, v1/notifications)
├── services/           # External API integration (M-Pesa, Cloudinary, EmailJS)
├── utils/              # Helper functions (geo-calculations, price formatters)
└── server.js           # Server initialization

II. DATABASE GUIDE (MONGOOSE SCHEMAS)
-------------------------------------

1. User Schema (Unified for Tenant/Owner/Admin):
   - name: String (required)
   - email: String (unique, required)
   - password: String (hashed)
   - userType: String (Enum: 'tenant', 'landlord', 'admin')
   - verified: Boolean (default: false)
   - personalInfo: { phone: String, bio: String, idNumber: String }
   - reputation: { score: Number, ratings: [ObjectId], avgRating: Number }
   - activeBadges: [String] (Allocated by logic or admin)

2. House Schema (Property Owner focus):
   - landlord: ObjectId (ref: User)
   - title: String (required)
   - houseType: String (Enum: 'bedsitter', 'single', '1br', '2br', '3br')
   - location: { area: String, coordinates: { lat: Number, lng: Number } }
   - pricing: { rent: Number, deposit: Number }
   - media: { coverImg: String, gallery: [String] (Max: 8) }
   - amenities: [String] (Enum-based check)
   - status: String (Enum: 'available', 'taken', 'pending_approval')
   - stats: { views: Number, favoriteBy: [ObjectId] }

3. Marketplace Item Schema:
   - seller: ObjectId (ref: User)
   - title: String (required)
   - category: String (Furniture, Electronics, etc.)
   - condition: String (New, Like-New, Used)
   - pricing: { price: Number }
   - media: { coverImg: String, gallery: [String] (Max: 3-4) }
   - status: String (Enum: 'active', 'sold', 'expired')

4. Admin Log Schema (Activity Tracking):
   - adminId: ObjectId (ref: User)
   - actionType: String (Enum: 'approve_listing', 'reject_listing', 'verify_user', 'broadcast', 'suspend_user', etc.)
   - targetId: String (The UUID of the affected entity)
   - description: String
   - canUndo: Boolean (default: true)
   - timestamp: Date

III. ENVIRONMENT KEYS (.env.REQUIRED)
--------------------------------------

1. AUTHENTICATION:
   - PORT = 5000
   - JWT_SECRET = [A long, secure string]
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID = [From Google Console]

2. DATABASE:
   - MONGO_URI = [MongoDB Atlas Connection String]

3. MEDIA & STORAGE:
   - CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME = [Account Name]
   - CLOUDINARY_API_KEY = [Public Key]
   - CLOUDINARY_API_SECRET = [Private Key]

4. PAYMENTS & CONTACT:
   - MPESA_CONSUMER_KEY = [Safaricom Daraja API]
   - MPESA_CONSUMER_SECRET = [Safaricom Daraja API]
   - MPESA_SHORTCODE = [Till/Paybill number]
   - EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID = [Service ID]
   - EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID = [Template ID]

================================================================================
END OF INFRASTRUCTURE GUIDE
================================================================================
